WEBVTT

00:00.100 --> 00:03.500
♪ WHEN THIS BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:03.500 --> 00:06.300
♪ BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:06.300 --> 00:10.500
♪ WANDERIN' DOWN THIS ROAD
THAT WE CALL LIFE ♪

00:10.500 --> 00:12.600
♪ IS WHAT WE'RE DOIN' ♪

00:12.600 --> 00:14.500
♪ IT'S GOOD TO KNOW
I HAVE FRIENDS ♪

00:14.500 --> 00:16.300
♪ WHO WILL ALWAYS ♪

00:16.300 --> 00:18.700
♪ STAND BY ME ♪

00:18.700 --> 00:22.233
♪ WHEN THIS BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:23.834 --> 00:25.233
YOU'LL NEVER GUESS!

00:25.233 --> 00:26.567
TOPANGA'S PREGNANT!

00:26.567 --> 00:28.467
SHE IS?!

00:28.467 --> 00:31.767
W-WHY'D SHE TELL
<i>YOU AND NOT ME?!</i>

00:31.767 --> 00:34.800
ARE YOU THE FATHER
OF MY CHILD?!

00:34.800 --> 00:37.000
HEY, IDIOT, YOU HAD NEWS?

00:37.000 --> 00:38.834
OH, YEAH. OKAY --

00:38.834 --> 00:40.200
I GOT A JOB!

00:40.200 --> 00:42.133
HEY, A JOB!
GOOD FOR YOU!

00:42.133 --> 00:44.100
ASK ME WHAT MY HOURS ARE.
GO AHEAD.

00:44.100 --> 00:45.600
WHAT ARE YOUR HOURS?

00:45.600 --> 00:46.867
IT'S UP TO ME!

00:46.867 --> 00:49.033
NOW ASK ME WHO I WORK FOR.

00:49.033 --> 00:50.300
YOU KNOW WHAT I WONDER?

00:50.300 --> 00:51.300
WHAT, WHAT, WHAT, WHAT?

00:51.300 --> 00:52.500
WHO YOUR BOSS COULD BE.

00:52.500 --> 00:54.400
ME! I WORK FOR ME!

00:54.400 --> 00:57.400
MY BOSS IS MR. ME!
IT'S ALL ME!

00:57.400 --> 00:59.000
ISN'T THAT GREAT?

00:59.000 --> 01:00.500
I WOULDN'T LIKE IT,
BUT IT'S GOOD FOR YOU.

01:00.500 --> 01:03.000
IT IS, SHAWN.
OH, YES, IT IS.

01:03.000 --> 01:06.700
AND I CAN MAKE BETWEEN $400
AND $5,000 A MONTH!

01:06.700 --> 01:08.200
OH, NO.

01:08.200 --> 01:10.400
YOU SEE,
I'M THE LORD OF MY CASTLE,

01:10.400 --> 01:13.367
AND AS THE LORD, I THINK
IT'S UP TO ME TO PROVIDE.

01:13.367 --> 01:14.600
AND IT'S UP TO TOPANGA

01:14.600 --> 01:17.734
TO BE MY GRATEFUL FRENCH
CHAMBERMAID, FIFI LeBANZA.

01:17.734 --> 01:20.734
YOU HAVEN'T ACTUALLY SAID THIS
TO TOPANGA, HAVE YOU?

01:20.734 --> 01:23.700
NAH, THIS IS JUST CRAP
FLOATIN' AROUND IN MY HEAD.

01:23.700 --> 01:26.200
BUT THAT'S
THE BEAUTY OF MARRIAGE, SHAWN.

01:26.200 --> 01:27.900
NOBODY
HAS TO KNOW NOTHIN'!

01:27.900 --> 01:28.934
I HAVE NEWS!

01:28.934 --> 01:30.000
<i>I </i>HAVE NEWS!

01:30.000 --> 01:31.800
ME FIRST?
LIKE ALWAYS.

01:31.800 --> 01:33.567
I WAS TAKIN' THE TRAIN
DOWNTOWN

01:33.567 --> 01:34.867
TO CHECK OUT SOME SHOES,

01:34.867 --> 01:36.900
AND I WAS SITTING
NEXT TO THIS WOMAN

01:36.900 --> 01:38.867
WHO WAS LOOKING
AT FASHION PHOTOS,

01:38.867 --> 01:40.967
AND I COMMENTED,
"OH, I LOVE THAT OUTFIT."

01:40.967 --> 01:42.567
SO DID SHE.

01:42.567 --> 01:44.734
TURNS OUT SHE'S THE EDITOR
FOR THIS FASHION MAGAZINE,

01:44.734 --> 01:48.200
AND WE HIT IT OFF SO WELL,
SHE OFFERED ME A JOB!

01:48.200 --> 01:50.867
I'M HER ASSISTANT, CORY!
I GOT A JOB!

01:54.467 --> 01:57.200
I'M REALLY
VERY PROUD OF YOU.

01:57.200 --> 01:58.834
WHAT'S YOUR NEWS?

01:58.834 --> 02:01.734
AH, I-I GOT A JOB, TOO.

02:01.734 --> 02:04.100
AAAAAAH! THAT'S GREAT!
WE'RE A 2-INCOME FAMILY!

02:04.100 --> 02:06.133
TELL ME EVERYTHING!
WHAT'S THE JOB?

02:06.133 --> 02:08.467
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY,
SO I'M WALKIN' DOWN THE STREET,

02:08.467 --> 02:10.967
AND I SEE THIS FLIER
WITH THE DOLLAR SIGNS ON IT.

02:10.967 --> 02:12.033
GO ON.

02:12.033 --> 02:13.200
SO I CALLED THE NUMBER.

02:13.200 --> 02:14.567
THAT'S GREAT!
THAT SHOWS INITIATIVE!

02:14.567 --> 02:16.600
NOW I'M AN ENTREPRENEUR!

02:16.600 --> 02:19.000
WHAT EXACTLY
ARE YOU DOING, SWEETIE?

02:19.000 --> 02:23.600
SELLING MAGAZINE SUBSCRIPTIONS
OVER THE PHONE!

02:23.600 --> 02:24.967
OH.

02:24.967 --> 02:26.500
OH.
TRY AGAIN.

02:26.500 --> 02:27.467
OHHH!

02:27.467 --> 02:29.200
OHHH!
GOOD GIRL.

02:29.200 --> 02:31.300
I CAN WEAR WHAT I WANT,
GO TO THE BATHROOM WHERE I WANT,

02:31.300 --> 02:33.600
I CAN EAT LUNCH
<i>WHEN </i>I WANT,

02:33.600 --> 02:36.100
AND I CAN MAKE
AS MUCH AS I CHOOSE

02:36.100 --> 02:38.467
BETWEEN $400
AND $5,000 A MONTH!

02:38.467 --> 02:40.500
I CHOOSE $5,000!
THANK YOU!

02:40.500 --> 02:42.700
WHERE ARE YOU WORKING?
WHERE ARE YOUR OFFICES?

02:42.700 --> 02:43.700
IN OUR LIVING ROOM.

02:43.700 --> 02:44.600
OH.

02:44.600 --> 02:45.700
OH.
TRY AGAIN.

02:45.700 --> 02:46.600
OH.

02:46.600 --> 02:47.967
OH.
NOT AS GOOD.

03:08.200 --> 03:10.734
HEY, LOOK -- A PENNY!

03:10.734 --> 03:12.033
HEY, WAS IT HEADS UP?

03:12.033 --> 03:15.567
IS THAT THE SIDE
WITH THE HEAD ON IT?

03:15.567 --> 03:16.900
YEAH.

03:16.900 --> 03:18.400
OH. YEAH, IT WAS HEADS UP.

03:18.400 --> 03:19.867
WELL...

03:19.867 --> 03:21.033
THEN YOU, MY FRIEND,

03:21.033 --> 03:22.734
ARE THE PROUD OWNER
OF A LUCKY PENNY.

03:22.734 --> 03:24.400
WHAT?! WHAT, REALLY?!

03:24.400 --> 03:29.400
I'VE NEVER HAD ONE OF THESE!
WHAT ARE THE RULES?

03:29.400 --> 03:31.734
IT'S EASY, ALL RIGHT?
IT'S JUST A SUPERSTITION.

03:31.734 --> 03:33.600
NO, NO --
I FEEL SOMETHING.

03:33.600 --> 03:36.734
I FELT SOMETHING THE SECOND
I TOUCHED THIS PENNY.

03:36.734 --> 03:38.800
WHY CAN'T YOU REACT
LIKE A NORMAL PERSON?

03:38.800 --> 03:42.800
I AM LUCKY!!

03:42.800 --> 03:44.500
WHAT NOW? [ LAUGHS ]

03:44.500 --> 03:46.000
OH, HE FOUND A SHINY PENNY.

03:46.000 --> 03:48.000
DO YOU WANT TO SEE
MY LUCKY PENNY?

03:48.000 --> 03:49.367
NO!

03:49.367 --> 03:51.133
<i>MY </i>LUCKY PENNY!

03:51.133 --> 03:53.500
WOW! THIS MUST BE
YOUR LUCKY DAY, ERIC.

03:53.500 --> 03:55.233
NO, NO, NO. Shh.

03:55.233 --> 03:59.100
NOT MY LUCKY DAY --
MY LUCKY LIFE.

03:59.100 --> 04:01.400
IT'S A NICE PENNY.
[ LAUGHS ]

04:05.667 --> 04:08.000
I SEE
WHAT YOU'RE TRYIN' TO DO.

04:08.000 --> 04:10.834
YOU'RE TRYIN' TO SEDUCE ME
FOR MY PENNY.

04:10.834 --> 04:13.100
YOU CAUGHT ME.

04:13.100 --> 04:16.400
I'M HOT FOR YOUR PENNY.

04:16.400 --> 04:18.367
EVIL TEMPTRESS.

04:18.367 --> 04:19.967
WELL, THAT'S ME.

04:19.967 --> 04:24.367
SEE, IF YOU HAD A NICKEL,
I'D PROBABLY MARRY YOU.

04:24.367 --> 04:27.000
THAT'S HOW BADLY
I WANT YOU!

04:27.000 --> 04:30.600
DUDE, GIMME A NICKEL!

04:30.600 --> 04:33.500
HELLO.

04:33.500 --> 04:37.867
IS THIS MR. LEON...SCHANAZZI?

04:37.867 --> 04:39.867
CAN YOU READ?

04:39.867 --> 04:42.400
GOOD FOR YOU...

04:42.400 --> 04:44.867
BECAUSE I'M GONNA READ YOU
OUR LIST OF MAGAZINES.

04:44.867 --> 04:47.800
NOW, THERE'S 700 HERE, SO PLEASE
DON'T HANG UP BEFORE I FINISH,

04:47.800 --> 04:49.834
BECAUSE I DON'T LIKE IT
AND IT'S MEAN TO ME.

04:49.834 --> 04:53.000
READY? HERE WE GO --

04:53.000 --> 04:55.300
<i>AARDVARK --</i>

04:55.300 --> 04:57.300
HELLO?

04:57.300 --> 04:59.200
HELLO?

05:06.500 --> 05:09.300
I TOLD YOU NOT TO DO THAT,
SCHANAZZI.

05:09.300 --> 05:12.467
NOW WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO START
ALL OVER AGAIN.

05:12.467 --> 05:14.467
HERE WE GO --

05:14.467 --> 05:16.600
<i>AARDVARK --</i>

05:16.600 --> 05:18.800
HELLO?

05:18.800 --> 05:21.767
SCHANAZZI?

05:30.700 --> 05:33.133
YOU KNOW WHAT, SCHANAZZI?

05:33.133 --> 05:35.500
YOU HAVE A STUPID NAME!

05:35.500 --> 05:38.567
CORY, YOU'LL NEVER GUESS
WHAT HAPPENED AT WORK TODAY!

05:38.567 --> 05:41.000
I CAN'T TALK NOW, SCHANAZZI.
MY WIFE'S HOME.

05:41.000 --> 05:42.400
I'LL CALL YOU LATER.

05:42.400 --> 05:45.767
CORY, I HAVE THE BEST NEWS!
I CAN'T WAIT TO TELL YOU!

05:45.767 --> 05:50.000
THIS...IS GONNA BE
THE KIND OF JOB

05:50.000 --> 05:52.767
WHERE I TAKE ASPIRIN...

05:52.767 --> 05:54.300
A LOT!

05:54.300 --> 05:56.500
HOW YOU DOIN'?

06:09.567 --> 06:11.200
HELLO?

06:11.200 --> 06:14.767
HI! IS THIS, UH,
DONNA SANTIANGELO?

06:14.767 --> 06:17.800
OH, GREAT!
THIS IS TOPANGA.

06:17.800 --> 06:21.200
OH, YOU'RE SO SWEET.
DONNA'S A GREAT NAME, TOO.

06:21.200 --> 06:24.367
UH, ANYWAY, I'M ONE OF THOSE
ANNOYING MAGAZINE PEOPLE

06:24.367 --> 06:26.100
WHO CALL AT THE WORST TIME.

06:26.100 --> 06:28.200
I KNOW.
DON'T YOU JUST HATE US?

06:28.200 --> 06:30.467
YEAH! LIKE YOU'RE
GONNA SELL A MAGAZINE!

06:30.467 --> 06:33.100
I COULDN'T SELL ONE MAGAZINE,
AND I'M IN THE BUSINESS!

06:33.100 --> 06:34.300
WHAT?

06:34.300 --> 06:37.600
UM...YEAH,
THAT'S ONE OF OUR MAGAZINES.

06:37.600 --> 06:39.233
UH-HUH. AND THAT.

06:39.233 --> 06:41.800
ALL OF THEM?
FANTASTIC!

06:41.800 --> 06:43.233
WE'LL BILL YOU!

06:43.233 --> 06:44.500
[ LAUGHS ]

06:44.500 --> 06:46.367
THAT WAS FUN!

06:46.367 --> 06:49.100
YOU SOLD A MAGAZINE?

06:49.100 --> 06:51.767
EIGHT. YOU MUST HAVE SOLD,
LIKE,<i>800!</i>

06:51.767 --> 06:54.967
HOW MANY DID YOU SELL?
TELL ME, TELL ME.

06:54.967 --> 06:57.200
PERHAPS YOU DIDN'T HEAR ME
WHEN I SAID,

06:57.200 --> 07:00.667
"I DIDN'T SELL ONE MAGAZINE,
AND I'M IN THE BUSINESS,"

07:00.667 --> 07:01.967
17 SECONDS AGO.

07:01.967 --> 07:04.700
RIGHT. SO, JUDY --
SHE'S MY BOSS --

07:04.700 --> 07:07.400
SHE CALLS ME INTO HER OFFICE
WITH TWO OTHER EDITORS.

07:07.400 --> 07:10.200
SHE ASKS FOR MY OPINION ON
WHAT OUR FIRST COVER SHOULD BE.

07:10.200 --> 07:12.100
THE OTHER TWO
<i>HATED </i>THE ONE I PICKED,

07:12.100 --> 07:13.934
BUT JUDY<i>LOVED</i>
THE ONE I PICKED,

07:13.934 --> 07:16.000
AND WE'RE GONNA USE
THE ONE I PICKED!

07:16.000 --> 07:19.300
CAN YOU BELIEVE IT?!
ME! THE ONE I PICKED!

07:19.300 --> 07:21.300
SO SHE PROMOTED YOU?

07:21.300 --> 07:23.600
YES!
ISN'T THAT SOMETHING?!

07:29.033 --> 07:32.600
EVERYBODY RELAX!
NOTHING BAD CAN HAPPEN TO YOU.

07:32.600 --> 07:35.033
YOU'RE WITH ME.

07:35.033 --> 07:36.467
WHAT'S GOIN' ON OVER THERE?

07:36.467 --> 07:37.800
HE FOUND A LUCKY PENNY.

07:37.800 --> 07:39.233
YOU REALLY
BELIEVE IN THAT STUFF?

07:39.233 --> 07:40.967
YES, SHAWN, YES, I DO.

07:40.967 --> 07:43.467
I'M THE CHOSEN ONE.
I'M PROTECTED.

07:43.467 --> 07:47.400
I'VE GOT AN INVISIBLE SHIELD
ALL OVER MY BODY.

07:47.400 --> 07:49.400
WATCH THIS.

07:49.400 --> 07:50.567
ROCCO!

07:50.567 --> 07:52.200
NO, PLEASE!
I DON'T WANT TO GET HURT!

07:52.200 --> 07:54.467
[ Singsong voice ]
ROCCO! ROCCO!

07:54.467 --> 07:56.400
I JUST<i>HATE </i>GETTING HURT!

07:56.400 --> 07:58.600
YOU BETTER HAVE A GOOD REASON
FOR BOTHERIN' ME.

07:58.600 --> 07:59.934
LET'S GO! LET'S GO!

07:59.934 --> 08:02.900
I JUST WANT ROCCO
TO CLEAR SOMETHING UP FOR ME.

08:02.900 --> 08:04.834
IF IT'S YOUR COMPLEXION,
NO CAN DO!

08:04.834 --> 08:06.900
HA HA HA! MY COMPL--

08:06.900 --> 08:08.200
LET'S GO! COME ON!

08:08.200 --> 08:11.567
NO, JUST REAL QUICK,
JUST REAL QUICK.

08:11.567 --> 08:16.033
JUST CURIOUS,
AS AN ATHLETE
ON THE FOOTBALL TEAM,

08:16.033 --> 08:18.133
IS IT A DISTRACTION
BEING GAY?

08:25.900 --> 08:26.967
THANK YOU.

08:26.967 --> 08:28.767
IT'S OKAY.
WHAT?

08:28.767 --> 08:33.133
I'VE BEEN HOLDING IT IN
FOR SO LONG.

08:33.133 --> 08:37.867
FELLAS, I'M GAY.

08:37.867 --> 08:39.200
THAT'S OKAY, ROCCO.
SO ARE WE.

08:39.200 --> 08:42.367
REALLY?
OH, SURE.

08:44.734 --> 08:47.033
WHAT?

08:47.033 --> 08:49.400
THIS IS IMPOSSIBLE!

08:49.400 --> 08:50.900
OH, HEY.

08:50.900 --> 08:53.033
JUST MOVE THE 9
TO THE 10...

08:53.033 --> 08:55.400
JACK TO THE QUEEN...

08:55.400 --> 08:57.567
OOH! LOOK!
I GOT AN ACE.

08:57.567 --> 08:59.500
I WIN.

09:02.200 --> 09:06.000
GOOD JOB, CORY.

09:06.000 --> 09:08.367
YEAH, I'M BRILLIANT.

09:08.367 --> 09:11.834
WELL, WORK MUST BE GOING WELL
IF YOU CAN TAKE A BREAK.

09:11.834 --> 09:15.600
YEAH, WELL, I --
I TOOK A LONG BREAK,
YOU KNOW?

09:15.600 --> 09:17.300
I-I QUIT.

09:17.300 --> 09:19.834
YOU QUIT?! WHY?!

09:19.834 --> 09:24.100
BECAUSE, TOPANGA, UNLIKE YOU,
I...WASN'T ENJOYING IT.

09:24.100 --> 09:26.934
UNLIKE YOU,
I WASN'T GOOD AT IT.

09:26.934 --> 09:30.200
UNLIKE YOU,
I DON'T SHINE AT EVERYTHING.

09:30.200 --> 09:32.600
I-I-I DON'T SHINE
AT<i>ANYTHING.</i>

09:32.600 --> 09:34.467
HONEY,
WHAT'S BOTHERING YOU?

09:34.467 --> 09:35.767
NOTHING, TOPANGA.

09:35.767 --> 09:37.500
I'M JUST --
I'M IN A MOOD, OKAY?

09:37.500 --> 09:40.200
WELL, IS THERE ANYTHING
I CAN DO TO CHEER YOU UP?

09:40.200 --> 09:43.000
TOPANGA KNOW
WHAT CORY LIKE.

09:43.000 --> 09:44.000
NO.

09:44.000 --> 09:45.834
BUT I LOVE YOU.

09:45.834 --> 09:47.000
WANNA GO HOME? HUH?

09:47.000 --> 09:49.100
YOU WANNA GO HOME
AND HAVE POOKY-POOK?

09:49.100 --> 09:51.967
NO, TOPANGA.
NO POOKY-POOK.

09:51.967 --> 09:53.233
WHY NOT?

09:53.233 --> 09:56.200
BECAUSE Y-YOU'RE BETTER
AT POOKY-POOK

09:56.200 --> 09:57.567
THAN I AM, TOO.

09:57.567 --> 09:59.367
Rachel:
OH, LOOK HOW CUTE!

09:59.367 --> 10:01.467
THEY'RE HAVING
THEIR FIRST FIGHT!

10:01.467 --> 10:04.100
CORY, I DON'T LIKE THAT
YOU CAN'T TALK TO ME ABOUT THIS.

10:04.100 --> 10:06.667
TOPANGA, LOOK, I JUST --

10:06.667 --> 10:12.033
I-I DON'T WANT TO SAY ANYTHING
THAT I'M GONNA REGRET, OKAY?

10:12.033 --> 10:13.800
DO YOU THINK
MAYBE WE SHOULD LEAVE?

10:13.800 --> 10:17.300
NO, NO. I WANNA SEE TOPANGA
MAKE CORY CRY.

10:17.300 --> 10:18.800
WHATEVER BUG YOU HAVE
UP YOUR BUTT,

10:18.800 --> 10:20.600
WHY ARE YOU BLAMING IT ON ME?

10:20.600 --> 10:24.100
TOPANGA, IF YOU'RE AS SMART
AS YOUR "A" STREAK SAYS YOU ARE,

10:24.100 --> 10:26.700
YOU'D KNOW JUST TO
LEAVE ME ALONE RIGHT NOW.

10:26.700 --> 10:28.100
THIS IS ABOUT MY GRADES?

10:28.100 --> 10:29.867
THIS IS<i>NOT</i>
<i>ABOUT YOUR GRADES!</i>

10:29.867 --> 10:31.400
YES, IT<i>IS!</i>

10:31.400 --> 10:35.467
I-IT'S ABOUT HOW YOU SHOVE
YOUR STUPID GRADES IN MY FACE

10:35.467 --> 10:37.300
OR HOW<i>YOU </i>GET PROMOTED

10:37.300 --> 10:41.000
OR -- OR<i>YOU </i>SELL
ONE OF<i>MY </i>SUBSCRIPTIONS.

10:41.000 --> 10:42.834
WELL, I'M SORRY
I TRIED TO HELP YOU

10:42.834 --> 10:44.734
WITH YOUR LITTLE
MAGAZINE PROJECT.

10:44.734 --> 10:46.600
IT'S<i>NOT </i>A PROJECT, OKAY?

10:46.600 --> 10:48.800
STICKER BOOKS
ARE A PROJECT.

10:48.800 --> 10:50.467
THIS IS MY<i>CAREER!</i>

10:50.467 --> 10:52.700
CORY, COME ON.
IT WASN'T YOUR CAREER.

10:52.700 --> 10:53.967
SHUT UP!
YOW!

10:53.967 --> 10:56.600
MYLIFE IS JUST AS IMPORTANT
AS<i>YOUR </i>LIFE,

10:56.600 --> 10:58.400
EVEN IF I DON'T DO MY LIFE
AS GOOD AS YOU!

10:58.400 --> 11:00.200
AS WELL AS YOU.
WHAT?

11:00.200 --> 11:03.400
I WAS JUST SAYING THAT
IT'S NOT AS GOOD AS YOU --

11:03.400 --> 11:05.100
ARE YOU CRAZY, TOPANGA?!

11:05.100 --> 11:08.400
ARE YOU KIDDING ME
THAT YOU WOULD SAY THAT NOW?

11:08.400 --> 11:10.200
CORY, THIS WHOLE
THING IS CRAZY!

11:10.200 --> 11:11.400
YEAH, IT REALLY IS --

11:11.400 --> 11:12.400
SIT DOWN!!

11:12.400 --> 11:13.600
YOW!

11:13.600 --> 11:17.567
AT LEAST I'M NOT
A HOITY-TOITY PHOTO ASSISTANT

11:17.567 --> 11:19.200
KISS JUDY'S TUSHIE!

11:21.834 --> 11:24.233
MAYBE I HAVE TO KISS
JUDY'S TUSHIE

11:24.233 --> 11:27.767
BECAUSE YOU CAN'T SELL
ONE STINKIN' MAGAZINE!

11:30.200 --> 11:31.900
OKAY, THAT'S IT, YEAH.

11:34.200 --> 11:35.667
WHAT DID YOU JUST SAY?

11:37.900 --> 11:40.967
I JUST SAID THAT YOU HAVEN'T
BEEN DOING ALL THAT WELL...

11:40.967 --> 11:41.967
NO, NO,<i>NO!</i>

11:41.967 --> 11:44.000
THAT IS<i>NOT </i>WHAT YOU SAID!

11:44.000 --> 11:46.000
YOU SAID I'M A LOSER,
TOPANGA!

11:46.000 --> 11:49.200
I<i>KNOW </i>YOU SAID IT
'CAUSE I<i>HEARD </i>IT!

11:49.200 --> 11:51.667
I HEARD IT
FROM YOUR BIG MOUTH!

11:51.667 --> 11:54.133
OH!

11:54.133 --> 11:55.700
I HAVE A BIG MOUTH NOW?!

11:55.700 --> 11:57.967
YOU CAN'T EVEN
PLAY SOLITAIRE, IMBECILE!

12:00.200 --> 12:02.033
DID YOU HEAR THAT OKAY
FROM MY BIG MOUTH?!

12:02.033 --> 12:04.667
YOU KNOW WHAT, TOPANGA?
I<i>USED </i>TO BE ABLE TO.

12:04.667 --> 12:07.700
I USED TO BE ABLE TO DO A LOT
OF THINGS BEFORE I MARRIED YOU.

12:07.700 --> 12:09.367
CONGRATULATIONS!

12:09.367 --> 12:11.400
YOU KILLED MY SPIRIT!

12:17.500 --> 12:18.767
I WIN.

12:18.767 --> 12:21.900
YOU LEAVE, I WIN!

12:21.900 --> 12:23.100
BYE!

12:29.367 --> 12:31.233
AW, MAN.

12:38.834 --> 12:42.133
I SAID
SHE KILLED MY SPIRIT.

12:42.133 --> 12:45.000
WELL...MARRIAGE
IS A NEW SITUATION.

12:45.000 --> 12:47.400
THERE'S LOTS OF NEW STRESS
ON YOU.

12:50.300 --> 12:54.300
YOU KNOW, THIS IS
OUR FIRST FIGHT EVER.

12:54.300 --> 12:57.300
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO DO?

12:57.300 --> 12:59.467
WELL...

12:59.467 --> 13:01.000
SHE LEFT CRYING.

13:01.000 --> 13:04.200
MY MOTHER AND FATHER FOUGHT
ALL THEIR LIVES,

13:04.200 --> 13:06.800
AND ONE OF THEM
ALWAYS WALKED OUT.

13:06.800 --> 13:09.467
ONE DAY,
ONE OF THEM NEVER CAME BACK.

13:09.467 --> 13:13.600
IT'S<i>BAD, </i>IN MY EXPERIENCE,
WHEN SOMEONE WALKS OUT CRYING.

13:13.600 --> 13:16.467
SO, WHAT DO I DO?

13:16.467 --> 13:17.800
YOU GO HOME...

13:17.800 --> 13:20.200
YOU HOPE
SHE'S STILL THERE...

13:22.867 --> 13:25.133
OH, NO.

13:25.133 --> 13:28.200
IF SHE IS, YOU LOCK THE DOOR
AND HAVE IT OUT.

13:28.200 --> 13:32.367
LIKE A STEEL-CAGE MATCH?

13:32.367 --> 13:34.233
NO ONE LEAVES
UNTIL THE FIGHT'S OVER.

13:34.233 --> 13:38.600
I JUST -- I-I WISH
I HADN'T SAID WHAT I SAID.

13:38.600 --> 13:40.133
BUT YOU<i>DID.</i>

13:40.133 --> 13:42.100
SO, OBVIOUSLY,
<i>SOMETHING'S  </i>BOTHERING YOU.

13:42.100 --> 13:43.500
WHAT?

13:43.500 --> 13:45.000
DON'T FIGURE IT OUT WITH ME.

13:45.000 --> 13:46.400
THOSE DAYS ARE LONG GONE.

13:46.400 --> 13:49.100
THERE'S ONLY<i>ONE </i>PERSON
WHO CAN HELP YOU HERE.

13:49.100 --> 13:51.767
AND IT'S ME.

13:51.767 --> 13:54.300
ERIC...NO!

13:54.300 --> 13:56.200
WHY DON'T YOU CRAM IT,
TALKBOY?

13:56.200 --> 13:58.133
THAT'S ALL YOU'RE GOOD FOR,
IS TALK.

13:58.133 --> 14:01.000
"OH! TALKITY-TALK, TALKITY-TALK!
TALKITY-TALK! YAK!"

14:01.000 --> 14:03.700
"OOH, LOOK! TRAILER BOY'S
GOT ALL THE ANSWERS!"

14:03.700 --> 14:06.467
YOU KNOW SOMETHIN'? THERE'S
ONE THING YOU DON'T HAVE --

14:06.467 --> 14:08.467
BAM! PENNY!

14:11.100 --> 14:12.734
HEY.

14:12.734 --> 14:14.400
HEY.

14:14.400 --> 14:16.767
I LOVE YOU, CORY.
YOU'RE MY BROTHER.

14:16.767 --> 14:18.900
THAT'S WHY
I'M GONNA GIVE YOU MY PENNY.

14:18.900 --> 14:21.367
ERIC...

14:21.367 --> 14:23.300
T-THAT PENNY'S
BEEN SO LUCKY FOR YOU.

14:23.300 --> 14:26.367
NOW IT'S GONNA BE LUCKY
FOR YOU.

14:26.367 --> 14:28.400
IF I COULD JUST HAVE
A S-SECOND.

14:32.100 --> 14:35.000
THANK YOU, PENNY,
FOR ALL YOU'VE TAUGHT ME,

14:35.000 --> 14:37.500
FOR YOU HAVE TAUGHT ME
CONFIDENCE,

14:37.500 --> 14:41.500
AND WITH THAT CONFIDENCE, I KNOW
THAT I NO LONGER NEED LUCK.

14:41.500 --> 14:44.400
SO I INTEND TO GO ON MY LIFE...
PENNILESS.

14:46.767 --> 14:49.967
[ Voice breaking ]
PFFFF-FFFF-FFFF!

14:49.967 --> 14:51.767
OH, ERIC,
THAT'S -- THAT'S VERY NICE.

14:51.767 --> 14:53.000
ARE YOU SURE ABOUT THIS?

14:53.000 --> 14:54.000
MM-HMM.

14:54.000 --> 14:55.000
OKAY.

14:55.000 --> 14:56.867
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

14:56.867 --> 14:59.033
GOOD LUCK, OLD GAL.

14:59.033 --> 15:03.967
YOU SHOULD TAKE CARE OF HER...
AND YOURSELF.

15:03.967 --> 15:06.467
ALL RIGHT.

15:06.467 --> 15:08.600
BYE-BYE.

15:14.600 --> 15:18.100
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

15:18.100 --> 15:20.734
THAT'S WEIRD -- LOOKS LIKE RAIN.

15:20.734 --> 15:22.500
GOOD THING I'M INSIDE.

15:33.667 --> 15:34.900
WELL...

15:34.900 --> 15:37.133
AT LEAST I DIDN'T GET WET.

15:43.200 --> 15:45.100
THANK YOU.

15:45.100 --> 15:46.300
EHHH.

15:46.300 --> 15:47.500
EHHHH.

15:50.700 --> 15:53.400
OH, NO.

15:53.400 --> 15:56.300
TOPANGA?

15:56.300 --> 15:58.600
TOPANGA!

15:58.600 --> 15:59.734
I'M HERE.

15:59.734 --> 16:01.300
HI.

16:08.867 --> 16:10.467
YOU'RE PLAYING SOLITAIRE?

16:10.467 --> 16:12.800
YEAH...'CAUSE I WAS ALONE.

16:12.800 --> 16:15.200
I PLAYED 19 GAMES.

16:15.200 --> 16:16.100
DID YOU WIN 'EM ALL?

16:17.367 --> 16:19.600
SORRY.
YEAH.

16:19.600 --> 16:21.667
COULD YOU
PUT THE CARDS AWAY?

16:21.667 --> 16:23.100
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.

16:23.100 --> 16:26.233
OH. YOU HAVE SOMETHING
YOU WANT TO SAY TO ME NOW?

16:26.233 --> 16:30.300
I'M -- I'M SORRY
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED.

16:30.300 --> 16:33.867
I'M -- I'M DEEPLY,
DEEPLY...SORRY.

16:33.867 --> 16:35.033
YOU KNOW?

16:35.033 --> 16:36.367
AND, UH...

16:36.367 --> 16:39.834
I-I-I DO TAKE BACK
WHAT I SAID TO YOU.

16:43.300 --> 16:44.934
UH-HUH?

16:47.200 --> 16:50.200
T-THAT'S ALL I GET,
IS "UH-HUH"?

16:50.200 --> 16:52.834
TOPANGA,
I-I JUST APOLOGIZED.

16:52.834 --> 16:54.900
NOW IT'S<i>YOUR </i>TURN.

16:54.900 --> 16:57.000
NO! THAT'S NOT
THE WAY IT WORKS!

16:57.000 --> 16:58.867
I DON'T APOLOGIZE
GOOD ENOUGH, EITHER?

16:58.867 --> 17:00.600
OH, IS THAT WHAT THAT WAS?!

17:02.367 --> 17:04.900
YOU HAVEN'T SAID ANYTHING
FOR AN HOUR.

17:04.900 --> 17:06.500
I'M<i>AFRAID</i>
<i>TO SAY ANYTHING!</i>

17:06.500 --> 17:08.200
WHY?!
I DON'T KNOW!

17:08.200 --> 17:11.700
YOU KNOW.
I THINK I KNOW BETTER
WHETHER I KNOW OR NOT, OKAY?

17:11.700 --> 17:13.734
THEN I GUESS I KNOW YOU
BETTER THAN YOU DO.

17:13.734 --> 17:15.600
OF COURSE YOU DO, TOPANGA.

17:15.600 --> 17:17.500
UNLESS WE TELL EACH OTHER
WHAT'S GOING ON,

17:17.500 --> 17:18.800
THEN WE CANNOT BE TRUTHFUL.

17:18.800 --> 17:20.834
THIS IS OUR FIRST FIGHT.

17:20.834 --> 17:23.767
EVER.
THEN LET'S
MAKE IT MEAN SOMETHING.

17:23.767 --> 17:25.600
TELL ME WHAT'S GOING ON.

17:25.600 --> 17:27.000
YOU WANT THE TRUTH?
TRUTH.

17:27.000 --> 17:29.867
SIT DOWN. I'LL BE HAPPY
TO TELL YOU THE TRUTH.

17:29.867 --> 17:32.100
EVER SINCE I'VE KNOWN YOU --
OKAY --

17:32.100 --> 17:34.767
I HAD AN IDEA --
YOU HAD A BETTER ONE.

17:34.767 --> 17:37.734
I GOT A GOOD GRADE,
YOU GOT A BETTER ONE.

17:37.734 --> 17:40.400
I GET INTO PENNBROOK,
YOU GET INTO YALE!

17:40.400 --> 17:41.900
I DIDN'T GO
BECAUSE OF YOU!

17:41.900 --> 17:44.233
I UNDERSTAND THAT!
THAT'S ALL PART OF THIS.

17:44.233 --> 17:45.867
GO ON.

17:45.867 --> 17:47.000
SO I GOT A JOB,

17:47.000 --> 17:49.567
BUT YOU, OF COURSE,
GET A<i>BETTER ONE!</i>

17:49.567 --> 17:51.000
WHAT'S NEXT?

17:51.000 --> 17:54.834
I MEAN, TOPANGA, I-I UNDERSTAND
THAT YOU'RE BETTER THAN ME.

17:54.834 --> 17:57.934
BUT WHY DO YOU HAVE TO
SHOVE IT IN MY FACE?!

17:57.934 --> 18:00.867
YOU THINK
I'M BETTER THAN YOU?

18:00.867 --> 18:02.367
I<i>KNOW </i>YOU ARE.

18:02.367 --> 18:05.500
YOU MAKE ME NOT THINK
VERY MUCH OF MYSELF.

18:10.000 --> 18:13.200
I DO WHAT?

18:13.200 --> 18:15.100
[ Crying ]
I'VE KILLED YOUR SPIRIT.

18:15.100 --> 18:18.867
TOPANGA...DON'T.

18:18.867 --> 18:20.367
I'VE CAUSED YOU PAIN.

18:20.367 --> 18:22.934
NO. LOOK...I-I'M OKAY.

18:22.934 --> 18:25.500
I WOULD<i>NEVER</i>
WANT TO CAUSE YOU PAIN.

18:25.500 --> 18:27.100
I WANT YOU TO BE HAPPY.

18:27.100 --> 18:30.667
EVERYTHING I EVER DID
WAS JUST TRYING TO IMPRESS YOU.

18:30.667 --> 18:33.467
REALLY?

18:33.467 --> 18:36.367
NO.

18:36.367 --> 18:38.700
SOMETIMES.

18:38.700 --> 18:40.967
SOMETIMES FOR ME.

18:40.967 --> 18:42.934
MOSTLY FOR ME.

18:42.934 --> 18:45.100
TWICE FOR YOU.

18:45.100 --> 18:48.900
A LOT FOR YOU.

18:48.900 --> 18:52.033
WHY FOR ME?

18:52.033 --> 18:54.734
BECAUSE I ALWAYS KNEW
YOU WERE WORTH IT.

18:54.734 --> 18:57.233
WHY?

18:57.233 --> 18:59.700
BECAUSE YOU BELIEVED IN US.

18:59.700 --> 19:03.367
YOU WERE THE ONE WHO HELD
THIS RELATIONSHIP TOGETHER

19:03.367 --> 19:06.567
WHEN I WAS<i>AFRAID</i>
OF THIS RELATIONSHIP.

19:06.567 --> 19:12.767
YOU WERE THE ONE WHO TAUGHT ME
TO HAVE FAITH IN LOVE.

19:12.767 --> 19:13.700
ME?

19:15.500 --> 19:21.367
I DON'T WANT YOU TO EVER
FEEL BAD ABOUT YOURSELF.

19:21.367 --> 19:23.367
AND I DON'T WANT YOU
TO EVER HOLD YOURSELF BACK

19:23.367 --> 19:24.700
BECAUSE OF ME.

19:24.700 --> 19:26.500
SO WHAT DO WE DO?

19:26.500 --> 19:29.133
WE HAVE TO
SUPPORT EACH OTHER, TOPANGA.

19:29.133 --> 19:31.133
AND WE CAN'T BE AFRAID
TO FIGHT WITH EACH OTHER.

19:31.133 --> 19:33.834
BUT I'M SCARED OF YOU.

19:33.834 --> 19:36.300
CORY,
SOMETIMES IN OUR LIVES,

19:36.300 --> 19:38.300
<i>YOU'RE </i>GOING TO BE
DOING BETTER THAN ME

19:38.300 --> 19:41.300
OR<i>I'M </i>GOING TO BE
DOING BETTER THAN YOU.

19:41.300 --> 19:43.300
BUT IF EITHER ONE OF US
IS DOING WELL AT ALL,

19:43.300 --> 19:45.300
IT'S BECAUSE
WE LOVE EACH OTHER.

19:45.300 --> 19:47.200
WE HAVE TO ALWAYS
REMEMBER THAT.

19:47.200 --> 19:49.734
WE'RE NOT COMPETING.
WE'RE A TEAM.

19:49.734 --> 19:52.467
I WOULD NEVER
WANT TO KILL YOUR SPIRIT,

19:52.467 --> 19:55.667
BECAUSE I LOVE YOUR SPIRIT.

19:58.800 --> 20:00.200
ALL RIGHT, SCHANAZZI,

20:00.200 --> 20:02.100
NOW, YOU'RE GONNA BUY
A MAGAZINE.

20:02.100 --> 20:03.300
YOU KNOW WHY?

20:03.300 --> 20:04.867
BECAUSE I'M BRINGIN' IN
THE WIFE!

20:04.867 --> 20:06.033
YOU KNOW WHY?

20:06.033 --> 20:08.734
BECAUSE WHEN THE TWO OF US
WORK TOGETHER,

20:08.734 --> 20:10.500
AIN'T NOTHIN'
GONNA STOP US!

20:10.500 --> 20:11.600
HELLO?

20:11.600 --> 20:14.000
HI. I'M THE WIFE --
TOPANGA.

20:14.000 --> 20:16.300
WHAT?

20:16.300 --> 20:18.600
WELL, WHAT KIND OF A NAME
IS SCHANAZZI?!

20:18.600 --> 20:20.300
That's what I said.

20:20.300 --> 20:23.900
HE DOESN'T WANT TO TALK TO ME.
HE WANTS TO TALK TO YOU.

20:23.900 --> 20:28.400
ALL RIGHT, SCHANAZZI,
LET'S HAVE IT.

20:28.400 --> 20:29.467
YES...

20:29.467 --> 20:30.600
YEAH...

20:30.600 --> 20:32.133
UH-HUH...

20:32.133 --> 20:34.400
GOODBYE.

20:34.400 --> 20:35.834
WELL, WHAT DID HE SAY?

20:35.834 --> 20:38.734
HE JUST BOUGHT A ONE-YEAR
SUBSCRIPTION TO<i>AARDVARK!</i>

20:38.734 --> 20:41.934
WHY?
HE SAID I WAS THE MOST
PERSISTENT PERSON HE EVER MET!

20:41.934 --> 20:44.000
HE DID, HUH?

20:44.000 --> 20:45.100
YEAH.

20:45.100 --> 20:48.133
YOU KNOW, I-I THINK
IT WAS A COMPLIMENT.

20:54.600 --> 20:57.667
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

21:07.834 --> 21:09.100
PENNY.

21:24.300 --> 21:25.734
HELLO?
